title: Excessive Ram Usage
content:
Hello All! Hope you are having a great day!

Recently I noticed that the Firefox process takes about 36%(700MB) of my RAM. And this is only with 3-4 simple text websites.... For example: html-gmail, wikipedia.com, simple google search..... I am pretty sure that the entire source of these webpages can't take 700MBs

Also I have a single extension a simple "Tab Session Manager" which helps me save entire firefox session if i need to open them up later...

Is Firefox storing website data on my RAM to make websites load faster? Is there some way to limit this? as I may want to free up some RAM for other more RAM hungry applications.

I tried optimizing memory usage on "about:memory" but that did not help.

Thanks in Anticipation! :)

PS: I think the topic "network and security" is not appropriate, but this is my first question and I do not know how to change tags and topic after posting a question  :|

title: Firefox crashes and can't use the existing profile when relaunching
content:
Over the past week I've had this error popup a few times when Firefox is launched:

"You've launched an older version of Firefox. Using an older version of Firefox can corrupt bookmarks and browsing history already saved to an existing Firefox profile. To protect your information, create a new profile for this installation of Firefox."

I haven't yet spotted a pattern, but the most recent time it happened, I had the browser already open and either opened a new window or clicked Firefox in my start menu. The new window showed my homepage (blank tab) but was unresponsive: I couldn't type into the address bar, click a bookmark, or even close the window. The existing window was fine, so I closed that but had to kill Firefox in Task Manager.

When I relaunched Firefox, I got the above error message. Luckily I use Sync, so my many bookmarks are backed up. But of course all cookies have been deleted, so I have to login to websites again.

Firefox is up-to-date (84.0.1, 64-bit) and running on Windows 10 Enterprise. I even uninstalled, cleared out the data in AppData\Roaming\Mozilla (plus Local and LocalLow), and reinstalled.

As I said, this has happened a few times over the last week (3 or 4?) and is starting to get annoying now!

Any ideas? Thanks!
creator: gbull

creator: phil_moor

title: Add-Ons & Others
content: I have written numerous times regarding the fonts as well as other matters concerning Firefox. With regard to the fonts, I always kept wondering why certain fonts like Arial Black and Arial Bold have been removed from Options, Fonts and Colours, These two fonts are very useful for those with ageing eyesight. Another grouse of mine is the rate at which Firefox has been upgrading its browser, so much so that many providers of add-one just threw up their hands and surrender and in the process, tons of extremely good add-ons were simply discarded when they became unusable! I still have tons of past add-ons which I had downloaded but became unusable. I think that it is well neigh time or even past time that Firefox has a special unit just to work on providing in-house add-ons instead of leaving their browser users in the lurch by depending on third parties for the add-ons. I have also written many times about these issues over time and I think that Mozilla owe its users clarifications regarding these issues. Thank you. Regards,
creator: winstonysyap

title: Cambiar Icono/Animación de Conectando/Cargando de una pestaña
content:
Al solicitar un sitio en una pestaña aparece un pequeño ícono (anteriormente una ruedita dando vueltas, después un punto a manera de ping pong) que nos indica que tal pestaña está cargando. Realmente no me dí cuenta cuando pasó, pero de repente me aparece solamente el ícono de un reloj de arena, sin animación. He desinstalado firefox lo más profundo que he podido y sigue igual ¿Habrá alguna manera de reestablecer el ícono de la pelota rebotando de un lado al otro? He buscado los videos de las reseñas del nuevo firefox 84 y en ellos los que lo usan todavía tienen tal animación.

He leído que modificando/creando un archivo chrome.css puede arreglarse, pero la información estaba un poco extensa y en inglés. Mi duda es ¿En qué momento se desconfiguró? ¿Por qué el reestablecer no lo ha arreglado? Y obviamente, ¿Cómo solucionarlo?

title: Firefox 84 Locking up 1-2 seconds frequently/randomly.
content:
So as of the last update my browser has suddenly started to lock up for 1-2 seconds at a time refusing to do anything for that duration, and then resume as normal after. It doesn't matter if I'm browsing, looking at images or watching a video... they all freeze. Videos will continue playing however with no skip/pause in sound.

It doesn't matter if I'm opening new tabs, scrolling facebook, or just typing here.. it doesn't seem to care what I'm doing when it happens. As I've typed this I've had it happen twice now with no occurrence in another program.

I thought this was my hard drive failing at first, so I migrated everything to a different hard drive as well as the cache folder... and it still does it.

I thought it was a particular addon "Honey" as it is KNOWN for significant slow downs as it checks for prices/coupons and after disabling it nothing changed.

I next assumed it had something to do with the session storing(looking at disk activity), so I changed the interval from 15 seconds to 25 minutes and that did nothing.

I tried doing a "refresh" as well as starting without addons and neither of those had any affect, implying the base program without addons is the issue.

There is no significant CPU spike when this occurs. Really activity is 20% or less average. There is a significant disk spike when this occurs. RAM usage is average with no change. If this were a RAM issue I'd be seeing instability at random, and not a single program.

I'm not encountering this issue with other programs - only firefox.

As it happens randomly I can't "reproduce" it reliably, but it is continuous and will occur whether I do anything or not. To be said it is not doing this on my desktop... so I guess it could be some conflict with winblows but I haven't a clue what that might be.... if it is please let me know so I can kill it with extreme prejudice.
creator: jax.endsleigh

title: Ich bin seit jahren ein Fan von Firefox
content: ich bin ein Fan seit jahren von Firfox gewesen, doch seitdem Mozilla sich immer mehr in das System einbringt wird der Browser leider immer schlecht und ist nicht mehr das was ich von Ihm kannte. Jetzt hängt er macht nicht mal das was er soll und er ist mir zu Aufgeblasen geworden, mit den ganzen Dingen die dazugekommen sind. Leider wie oben schon Mitgeteilt hängt sich zu viel Morzilla als Firma mit rein. Wenn es nicht bald wieder eine änderung gibt, so werde ich den Browser tauschen müssen obwohl es mir sehr schwer fällt. Doch Mitlerweile läuft mein Browser Firefox unter meinem Debian immer schelchter als im gegensatz zu früher. Nicht nur das er so Aufgeblasen worden ist, nein er hat für meine Begriffe zu viele andere Hände im Spiel eben wie der Mutterkonzern Morzilla. Bitte das zu ändern, denn sonst verliert ihr in Deutschland sehr viele anhänger und das wäre doch echt schade. Daher kommt auf meinen alten Firefox zurück. Sonst muss ich Vivaldi und Brave eine Möglichkeit geben. Da mein Firefox nicht mehr der zuverlässige Browser ist wie bisher. Also trennen wieder von Morzilla bitte.

What I want to have, is a shortcut on my desktop to launch the window on the right of the attached screenshot without manually having to open Firefox -> Hamburger Menu -> Sites in App Mode -> <selecting site>

I'm using Ubuntu/PopOS 20 with latest version of Firefox Any help would be great. Thanks
